  "date_published": "2025-04-07",
  "body": "<html><body><div class=\"field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item\" property=\"schema:text\"><p><br/><strong>Presented by Debevoise &amp; Plimpton</strong></p><p><span>In 2024, property and casualty insurers faced heavy losses from frequent and severe natural catastrophes. Insurance companies in these markets may consider surplus notes as a means to raise capital for regulatory, operational, or strategic needs without increasing the liabilities reported on their statutory financial statements.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://www.debevoise.com/insights/publications/2025/03/surplus-notes-as-a-source-of-capital-for-p-c\"><span><strong>Learn more &gt;</strong></span></a></p></div></body></html>",
